[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scotland's politicians speak of their 2016 Christmas wishes

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scotland's political leaders tell the BBC what they want Santa to bring this Christmas.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
22 December 2016 Last updated at 13:57 GMT
They combined serious political hopes with more light-hearted wishes.
The country's First Minister Nicola Sturgeon; the Conservative's Ruth Davidson; Labour's Kezia Dugdale; Patrick Harvie from the Scottish Greens and the Lib Dems' Willie Rennie all took part.
